(139, 'Gigabyte 512MB 9600GT ', '', '<p>nVidia Geforce GDDR3 <br /> 2xDVI, 1xD-Sub, 1xHDMI<br />Dual Screen</p>', '<h2>Overview</h2>\r\n<p>NVIDIA''s ninth generation series of graphics cards brings cutting edge technology and advanced capabilities together for best-in-class performance. The 9600GT is the solution for all your graphic needs. It&rsquo;s Windows 7 ready and equipped with a PCI-Express 2.0 interface for the most up-to-date system.<br /> <br />Support for DirectX 10, Shader Model 4.0, OpenGL 2.0 and NVIDIA''s PureVideoHD technologies are also built in. The card''s core clock runs at 650MHz, relieving your CPU of pixel crunching duty. Data surges through the 9600''s 64 stream processors which are fed by 512MB of 256-bit 1800MHz GDDR3 memory. Twin dual-linked DVI and 400 MHz RAMDAC lets you display 2560 x 1600 resolution video and graphics on even the largest monitors. <br /><br /></p>\r\n<table width="615px">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Interface</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Interface</td>\r\n<td>PCI Express 2.0 x16</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Chipset</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Chipset Manufacturer</td>\r\n<td>NVIDIA</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>GPU</td>\r\n<td>GeForce 9600 GT</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Core Clock</td>\r\n<td>650MHz</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Stream Processors</td>\r\n<td>64</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Memory</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Memory Clock</td>\r\n<td>1800MHz</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Memory Size</td>\r\n<td>512MB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Memory Interface</td>\r\n<td>256-bit</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Memory Type</td>\r\n<td>GDDR3</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">3D API</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>DirectX</td>\r\n<td>DirectX 10</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>OpenGL</td>\r\n<td>OpenGL 2.1</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Ports</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>HDMI</td>\r\n<td>1 <br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>D-SUB</td>\r\n<td>1</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>DVI</td>\r\n<td>1 (2 with included adapter)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">General</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Max Resolution</td>\r\n<td>2560 x 1600</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>SLI Supported</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cooler</td>\r\n<td>Fanless</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>System Requirements</td>\r\n<td>Minimum 450W or greater system power supply (with a minimum 12V current rating of 24A)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Power Connector</td>\r\n<td>6 Pin</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Dual-Link DVI Supported</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>HDCP Ready</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Features</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Features</td>\r\n<td>Hot Ultra Durable VGA High Quality Component<br />New Passive Thermal Solution: Silent Cell<br />Native HDMI</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Manufacturer Warranty</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Parts</td>\r\n<td>3 years limited</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Labor</td>\r\n<td>3 years limited</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>', 110.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.20, 0, '2009-07-05 16:43:25', '', 0.00, '', 0.00, '', 0.00, 0, NULL),
(140, 'PNY 512MB NVS420 ', '', '<p>nVidia Quadro4 GDDR3<br /> 4xDVI (Not Fanless)<br />Quad Screen</p>', '<p><strong>NVIDIA Quadro NVS 420 by PNY  Technologies</strong> for x1 PCIE is a quad-display graphics solution that delivers a reliable hardware and software platform for your digital audio workstation. Featuring NVIDIA nView&trade; advanced display software technology and support for up to four 30&rdquo; displays at 1900 x 1200 resolution, recording professionals can maximize productivity through increased desktop real estate and advanced application management tools.</p>\r\n<p>Featuring CUDA&trade; parallel computing processors with a unified architecture designed to dynamically allocate GPU resources, the Quadro NVS 420 solution delivers optimized performanc. Capable of supporting up to four digital displays at resolutions of up to 1900 x 1200 through the supplied VHDCI to quad DVI-D SL adapter, the Quadro NVS 420 maximizes productivity by enabling more screen real estate from a single graphics card.</p>\r\n<p>Through the NVIDIA nView advanced display software, Quadro NVS 420 enables features such as profiles, extended Windows taskbar, gridlines, and virtual desktops. In addition, Quadro NVS 420 provides high-quality HD video output and high memory bandwidth for today&rsquo;s more demanding digital signage requirements. <br /><br /></p>\r\n<table width="615px">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Memory Size</strong></td>\r\n<td>512MB GDDR3 (256MB per GPU)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Memory Interface</strong></td>\r\n<td>128-bit (64-bit per GPU)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Memory Bandwidth</strong></td>\r\n<td>22.4GB/sec (11.2GB/Sec per GPU)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Max Digital Display Resolution</strong></td>\r\n<td>2560 x 1600</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Max Power Consumption</strong></td>\r\n<td>40W</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Graphics Bus</strong></td>\r\n<td>PCI Express x1</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Display Connectors</strong></td>\r\n<td>DVI-D Single Link (4)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Auxiliary Power Connectors</strong></td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Number of Slots</strong></td>\r\n<td>1</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Thermal Solution</strong></td>\r\n<td>Active Fansink</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<h2>Key Features and Benefits:</h2>\r\n<p><strong>NVIDIA Unified Architecture</strong><br /> Industry&rsquo;s first unified architecture designed to dynamically allocate GPU  resources to deliver optimized performance. <br /> <br /> <strong>NVIDIA CUDA Parallel Computing Processor</strong><br /> 16 CUDA parallel processing cores compatible with all CUDA accelerated applications. NVIDIA CUDA provides a C language environment and tool suite that unleashes new capabilities to solve various visualization challenges.<br /> <br /> <strong>Quad DVI-D Single Link</strong><br /> The NVS 420 for DVI features a VHDCI to quad DVI-D Single Link adapter that supports up to four DVI compatible digital displays at resolutions up to 1900 x 1200.<br /> <br /> <strong>NVIDIA PureVideo&reg; Technology</strong><br /> NVIDIA PureVideo technology is the combination of high-definition video processors and software that delivers unprecedented picture clarity, smooth video, accurate color, and precise image scaling for SD and HD video content. Features include high-quality scaling, spatial temporal de-interlacing, inverse telecine, and high quality HF video playback from DVD.<br /> <br /> <strong>NVIDIA nView Advanced Display Software</strong><br /> The nView advanced display software delivers maximum flexibility for single large display or multi-display configurations, providing unprecedented end-user control of the desktop experience for increased productivity.<br /> <br /> <strong>Energy Star Enabled Design</strong><br /> Enables Energy Star compliance with low maximum and low idle power levels.<br /><br /></p>', 460.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.20, 0, '2009-07-05 16:49:54', '', 0.00, '', 0.00, '', 0.00, 1, NULL),
