(158, 'Noctua NH-U9B', '', '<p>92mm fan<br /> Temp: 32&deg;C - 44&deg;C<br /> Noise: 16dB ~ 32dB</p>', '<p>The NH-U9B continues the legacy of Noctua''s classic NH-U coolers, which won over 150 awards and recommendations from leading international websites and magazines. Due to its compact size, the NH-U9B is perfect for HTPCs and small cases as well all as other applications that don''t provide sufficient space for its bigger brother NH-U12P. Bundled with Noctua''s award-winning NT-H1 thermal compound and fitted with the new NF-B9 fan, the NH-U9B offers outstanding quietness and excellent performance levels close to the NH-U12P.</p>\r\n<table width="615px">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Specifications</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Type</td>\r\n<td>Fan &amp; Heatsinks</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Fan Size</td>\r\n<td>92mm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Compatibility</td>\r\n<td>Socket 754 / 939 / 940 / AM2 / LGA775</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Bearing Type</td>\r\n<td>SSO</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>RPM</td>\r\n<td>Rotational Speed (+/- 10%)  1600 RPM<br />Rotational Speed with L.N.A. (+/- 10%)  1300 RPM <br />Rotational Speed with U.L.N.A. (+/- 10%)  1000 RPM</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Noise Level</td>\r\n<td>Acoustical Noise  17.6dB(A) <br />Acoustical Noise with L.N.A.  13.1 dB(A) <br />Acoustical Noise with U.L.N.A.  7.9 dB(A)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Heatsink Material</td>\r\n<td>Copper (base and heat-pipes), aluminium (cooling fins), soldered joints, nickel plated</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Physical Spec</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Fan Dimensions</td>\r\n<td>92 x 92 x 25mm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Weight</td>\r\n<td>550g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>', 55.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0, '2009-07-05 20:46:42', '', 0.00, '', 0.00, '', 0.00, 1, NULL),
(159, 'Zalman CNPS9900', '', '<p>120mm fan<br /> Temp: 32&deg;C - 45&deg;C<br /> Noise: 16dB ~ 38dB</p>', '<h2>High Performance CPU Cooler</h2>\r\n<p>Long popular for the design and engineering of their products, Zalman continues to deliver on their tradition by producing quality products backed with excellent service. The CNPS9900LED goes a step further by looking good as it cools your Intel processor. <br /> <br />The efficient dual copper heatsink design combines a patented 3-pipe system that effortlessly whisks heat away with the help of the 120mm blue LED fan&rsquo;s blades and 2 ball bearings. Noise level can be lessened automatically by using the integrated PWM functionality which lets the BIOS monitor fan performance and thermal need and adjust the fan''s speed accordingly.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width="615px">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Spec</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Type</td>\r\n<td>Fan &amp; Heatsinks</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Fan Size</td>\r\n<td>120mm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Bearing Type</td>\r\n<td>2 Ball</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>RPM</td>\r\n<td>1000 - 2000RPM &plusmn; 10%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Noise Level</td>\r\n<td>16dB - 38.0dB &plusmn; 10%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Heatsink Material</td>\r\n<td>Pure Copper</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Physical Spec</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Weight</td>\r\n<td>730g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>', 80.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0, '2009-07-05 20:59:29', '', 0.00, '', 0.00, '', 0.00, 0, NULL),
(160, 'Noctua NH-U12P', '', '<p>120mm fan<strong><br /> </strong>Temp 34&deg;C - 39&deg;C<strong><br /> </strong>Noise: 12dB ~ 20dB<br /><span style="font-family: ''Segoe UI'', Tahoma, Helvetica, Verdana, Arial, ''Trebuchet MS'', sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: #ff0000; font-style: italic; line-height: 14px;">Tower Cases Only!</span></p>', '<p>Intel''s new Core i7 CPUs mark an exciting advance in processing power, but they definitely require a high quality heatsink if you want to cool them without excessive noise. <br /> <br />Heat is drawn away from the CPU by the base of the copper heatsink and transferred up into the array of hi-grade aluminum fins for dissipation. A large 120mm fan spins on each side of the array blowing heated air away from the heatsink. The fans'' support for PWM lets the BIOS control the speed of the fan based on the CPU''s thermal needs &ndash; lowering the fans speed and noise during off-peak cycles.</p>\r\n<table width="615px">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Specifications</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Type</td>\r\n<td>Fan &amp; Heatsinks</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Fan Size</td>\r\n<td>120mm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Bearing Type</td>\r\n<td>SSO</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>RPM</td>\r\n<td>Rotational Speed (+/- 10%): 1300 RPM<br />Rotational Speed with L.N.A. (+/- 10%): 1100 RPM<br />Rotational Speed with U.L.N.A. (+/- 10%): 900 RPM</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Air Flow</td>\r\n<td>Airflow: 54.36 CFM<br />Airflow with L.N.A.: 46.23 CFM<br />Airflow with U.L.N.A.: 37.33 CFM</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Noise Level</td>\r\n<td>Acoustical Noise: 19.8 dB(A)<br />Acoustical Noise with L.N.A.: 16.9 dB(A)<br />Acoustical Noise with U.L.N.A.: 12.6 dB(A)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Heatsink Material</td>\r\n<td>Copper (base and heat-pipes), aluminium (cooling fins), soldered joints &amp; nickel plating</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Physical Spec</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Fan Dimensions</td>\r\n