(176, 'Apevia X-QPack', '', '<p>Micro-ATX w/Handle<br />3x3.5" HDD <br />2x5.25" ODD</p>', '<h2>Brief Description</h2>\r\n<p>If you are looking for a PC that is compact and dynamic that you can just grab and go, then this Apevia X-QPACK is your perfect choice. The X-QPACK is designed with the idea of giving users to choose any Micro ATX motherboard and components in the market to build their own compact PC. With 3 hard drive bays, 2 cd drive bays and a 120mm fan, this X-QPACK is powerful, cool yet quiet.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width="615px">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Spec</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Type</td>\r\n<td>MicroATX Desktop</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Color</td>\r\n<td>Black</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Case Material</td>\r\n<td>Aluminum Body/ Front Mask</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Motherboard Compatibility</td>\r\n<td>Micro ATX, Baby AT</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Expansion</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>External 5.25" Drive Bays</td>\r\n<td>2</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>External 3.5" Drive Bays</td>\r\n<td>1</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Internal 3.5" Drive Bays</td>\r\n<td>2</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Expansion Slots</td>\r\n<td>4</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>With front LCD display</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Front Ports</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Front Ports</td>\r\n<td>USB, Audio, IEEE 1394</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Cooling System</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>80mm Fans</td>\r\n<td>1 x 80mm UV Blue Front Fan</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>120mm Fans</td>\r\n<td>1 x 120mm UV Blue Rear Fan</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Side Air duct</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Physical Spec</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Dimensions(L x W x H)</td>\r\n<td>14.70" x 11.20" x 9.00"</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Weight (without components)<br /></td>\r\n<td>11 lbs.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2" class="tablehead">Features</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Features</td>\r\n<td>Compact Portable Stylish Design<br />Front LCD Temperature Display with Blue Back Lighting<br />Strong Steel Handle for Carrying around<br />Best Cooling for Micro ATX Case<br />Removable Motherboard Tray</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>', 70.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.05, 0, '2009-08-26 12:31:22', '', 0.00, '', 0.00, '', 0.00, 1, NULL),
(177, 'Antec Mini P-180', '', '<p>Micro-ATX<br />6x3.5" HDD<br />3x5.25" ODD</p>', '<p>The reliability, performance, and versatility of the Antec Performance One series is now available in a stylishly small enclosure, perfect for musician on the move. The Mini P180 boasts a heat-reducing dual chamber design with room for your microATX motherboard, power supply, and up to 5 hard drives. Sound-deadening multi-layer side panels and silicone grommets ensure quiet computing, while 120 mm and 200 mm fans provide optimal cooling. Top it off with a sleek interior black finish and front USB, audio, and eSATA ports, and you won''t believe the quality we''ve fit into this petite portable case.</p>', 115.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.05, 0, '2009-08-26 12:40:53', '', 0.00, '', 0.00, '', 0.00, 1, NULL),
